      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "Migrates the plugin from a bare JavaScript prototype to TypeScript, split into focused modules (recording, transcription, template rendering, settings) and bundled to main.js with esbuild. Fixes a filename-templating bug where an unbalanced placeholder (e.g. a stray `{{time}`) silently produced a malformed filename instead of being rejected. Adds store-readiness features required for Obsidian community plugin submission: masked API key storage, a folder-picker for note/audio save locations, a Markdown-file-based note template, graceful handling of mic disconnects and low-signal recordings, and a GitHub Actions release pipeline.\n\nNo breaking changes for existing users; settings from 0.1.0 migrate automatically.",
      "downloadCount": 22,
